OL,6,F"I can't see that I will ever be pain-
OL,7,Ffree," she said. "I just can't see
OL,8,Fthat that will ever happen. And that's
OL,9,Fsomething that sadly I've got to live
OL,10,Fwith and learn to cope with."
OL,12,FA representative for Mr Dixon did not
OL,13,Frespond to requests for a comment on
OL,14,FMs Hanman's case.
OL,16,FIn response to the Medical
OL,17,FPractitioners Tribunal findings
OL,18,Fagainst him, he said: "I have accepted
OL,19,Fthe findings of misconduct made
OL,20,Fagainst me by the Medical
OL,21,FPractitioners Tribunal.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
